title: Japan Airlines 777 makes extreme go around in strong crosswind
text:
Japan Airlines 777 makes extreme go around in strong crosswind Last updated 11:33, October 14 2015 Airlive.net/facebook 
This Boeing 777 was forced into a go around, due to an extreme crosswind. 
A video has shown the moment a Japan Airlines Boeing 777 was forced to make a go around due to extreme crosswinds. 
The clip, posted by Airlive.net, was captured as the aircraft tried to land at Tokyo's Narita airport. 
It shows the plane lurching from side-to-side as it is caught in strong winds. 
Japan Airlines Boeing 777 makes extreme go around at Narita airport (Tokyo) due to strong crosswind - by Tsurikitetsu
